s thinking on economic development and reform.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEconomic history. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh  aAlbert O. Hirschman.  aFederal Reserve Board.  aMarshall Plan.  aeconomic development.  aeconomic history.  aeconomic policy.  aeconomic recovery.  aeconomics.  ainternational economic order.  apostwar Europe.1 aAlacevich, Michele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlacevich, Michele, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAsso, Pier Francesco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAsso, Pier Francesco, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHinrichs, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirschman, Albert O., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311074966340uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/hirs2005840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231553698423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231553698/original  a978-3-11-074966-3  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK